10 An Act relating to vulnerable juveniles and adults;
defining terms; allowing the Office of Juvenile
11 Affairs, county juvenile detention centers, and the
Department of Human Services to hire temporary staff
12 members from certain agencies for a certain amount of
time; providing for codification; and providing an
13 effective date.
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-7-301.1 of Title 10A, unless
18 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. As used in this section:
20 1. "Contracting organization" means an organization which
21 operates under a written agreement signed between the Office of
22 Juvenile Affairs, Oklahoma Health Care Authority, or Department of
23 Human Services and an organization that provides direct care
24 workers, rather than full-time direct hire staff, to post-
HB3907 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 adju dication treatment facilities, residential care facilities
2 including intermediate care facilities for individuals with
3 intellectual disabilities (ICF-IID), daily living supports (DLS)
4 home or group homes;
5 2. "Temporary agency" means staffing agencies, part-time
6 staffing agencies, recruiting agencies, or other organizations that
7 provide employees on a temporary basis; and
8 3. "Vulnerable person" means any person under the age of
9 eighteen (18) or a person having an intellectual disability.
10 B. A group home, intermediate care facilities for individuals
11 with intellectual disabilities, daily living supports (DLS) home,
12 post-adjudication treatment facility, or any other facility holding
13 youth operated by the Office of Juvenile Affairs, Department of
14 Human Services, or contracted with the Oklahoma Health Care
15 Authority, may utilize, employ, or enter into an agreement to staff
16 facilities using organizations known as temporary agencies or
17 contracting organizations who employ full- or part-time team members
18 on behalf of the Office of Juvenile Affairs, Department of Human
19 Services, or the Oklahoma Health Care Authority on a temporary or
20 contract basis for no more than two (2) months for any single
21 position to be covered by a temporary staff member within a twelve-
22 month period and the agency utilizing the temporary staff member
23 shall be actively trying to fill the permanent position.
