1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 458.1 of Title 19, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. As used in this section:
5 1. "Contracting organization" means an organization which
6 operates under a written agreement signed between the Office of
7 Juvenile Affairs and an organization that provided contract workers,
8 rather than full-time direct hire staff, to post-adjudication
9 treatment facilities; and
10 2. "Temporary agency" means staffing agencies, part-time
11 staffing agencies, recruiting agencies, or other organizations that
12 provide employees on a temporary basis.
13 B. County juvenile detention centers may utilize, employ, or
14 enter into an agreement to staff detention facilities using
15 organizations known as temporary agencies or contracting
16 organizations who employ full- or part-time team members to the
17 county on a contract basis for no more than two (2) months for any
18 single position to be covered by a temporary staff member within a
19 twelve-month period and the agency utilizing the temporary staff
20 member shall be actively trying to fill the permanent position.
21 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
22 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 530.9 of Title 56, unless there
23 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
24 A. As used in this section:
