1 1. "Contracting organization" means an organization which
2 operates under a written agreement signed between the Office of
3 Juvenile Affairs and an organization that provided contract workers,
4 rather than full-time direct hire staff, to post-adjudication
5 treatment facilities; and
6 2. "Temporary agency" means staffing agencies, part-time
7 staffing agencies, recruiting agencies, or other organizations that
8 provide employees on a temporary basis.
9 B. An adult companion home certified by the Department of Human
10 Services may utilize, employ, or enter into an agreement to staff
11 facilities using organizations known as temporary agencies or
12 contracting organizations who employ full- or part-time team members
13 to the Department on a contract basis for no more than two (2)
14 months for any single position to be covered by a temporary staff
15 member within a twelve-month period and the agency utilizing the
16 temporary staff member shall be actively trying to fill the
17 permanent position.
18 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
